  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Application Test Engineer",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for Application Test Engineer  to design, execute, and lead performance testing initiatives for enterprise-scale applications. The successful candidate will work closely with architects, developers, and stakeholders to ensure system scalability, reliability, and performance meet business expectations.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities:</h3><ul><li><p>Define and implement <strong>performance testing strategies, plans, and scripts</strong> aligned with project requirements.</p></li><li><p>Collaborate with <strong>solution architects, developers, and business stakeholders</strong> to identify performance requirements, SLAs, and KPIs.</p></li><li><p>Lead <strong>performance, load, stress, and endurance testing</strong> activities across applications and platforms.</p></li><li><p>Analyse test results to identify <strong>performance bottlenecks, scalability issues, and system constraints</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Prepare and present <strong>detailed performance test reports</strong>, findings, and optimisation recommendations to technical and business teams.</p></li><li><p>Manage performance testing <strong>tools, test environments, test data, and execution schedules</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Support performance tuning efforts across application, database, and infrastructure layers.</p></li><li><p>Mentor junior testers and coordinate with <strong>regional or global QA teams</strong> to ensure testing standards and best practices are followed.</p></li></ul><h3>Required Skills & Experience:</h3><ul><li><p>Proven hands-on experience in <strong>performance testing and performance engineering</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Strong expertise in performance testing tools such as <strong>LoadRunner, JMeter, NeoLoad, or Gatling</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Proficiency in <strong>scripting and test development</strong> using languages such as <strong>Java, Python, or JavaScript</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Solid understanding of <strong>system architecture, application performance tuning, and monitoring concepts</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Experience working with performance metrics, monitoring tools, and log analysis.</p></li><li><p>Excellent <strong>analytical, communication, and stakeholder management</strong> skills.</p></li><li><p>Ability to work independently and collaboratively in a fast-paced project environment.</p></li></ul>",
